.TH "batadv_window_protected" 9 "batadv_window_protected" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_window_protected \- checks whether the host restarted and is in the protection time.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" batadv_window_protected
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "s32 seq_num_diff "  ","
.BI "s32 seq_old_max_diff "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *last_reset "  ","
.BI "bool *protection_started "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "seq_num_diff" 12
difference between the current/received sequence number and
the last sequence number
.IP "seq_old_max_diff" 12
maximum age of sequence number not considered as restart
.IP "last_reset" 12
jiffies timestamp of the last reset, will be updated when reset
is detected
.IP "protection_started" 12
is set to true if the protection window was started,
doesn't change otherwise.
.SH "RETURN"
false if the packet is to be accepted.
true if the packet is to be ignored.
